  "text": "The girth of a graph G, denoted as g(G), is the length of a shortest cycle with larger domination number. We refer the reader to [30] for a detailed survey 41 on this topic. In general it is NP -hard to determine the bondage number (see 42 Hu and Xu [CITATION_1] ), and thus useful to find bounds for it.",
